<title>NORWAY: Kvaerner Q1 pre-tax falls 59 pct. [CORRECTED 09:31 GMT]</title>
<headline>Kvaerner Q1 pre-tax falls 59 pct. [CORRECTED 09:31 GMT]</headline>
<dateline>OSLO 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31.</p>
<p>				  (millions of crowns unless stated)</p>
<p> Operating revenues		15,208     vs     7,660</p>
<p> Depreciation			   342     vs	 186</p>
<p> Operating profit		     442     vs	 593</p>
<p> Pre-tax profit			 224     vs	 537</p>
<p>(Corrects Q1 1997 pre-tax profit figure from 221 million crowns)</p>
<p> After-tax profit		     165     vs	 389</p>
<p>NOTE -- Full name of Anglo-Norwegian construction and engineering company is Kvaerner ASA. Kvaerner acquired British conglomerate Trafalgar House Plc in April last year. Comparative Q1 figures have been adjusted following the merger.</p>
<p>Nine Norwegian and international analysts forecast a first-quarter operating result of 331 million crowns and pre-tax profits of 149 million crowns.</p>
<p>--Oslo newsroom, +47 22 42 50 41</p>
